partitionedBy.description:
Partitioning configuration defines partitioned field and func we should apply to the current field get partitioned value. Both fields are required if this block is defined. Example:</p><code>create table table_name (
  id int,
  timestamp string,
  name string
) partitioned by (year string)
</code>Let’s assume our current field is timestamp. To define partitioning relation we should define partitionedBy block as</P<code>>{
  "field": "year",
  "function": "TIME"
}
</code></p>This example assumes that year field in composer has YEAR granularity
